quran[17]{c,v,t}:
  33,1,"O Prophet! ňĻAlwaysňļ be mindful of God, and do not yield to the disbelievers and the hypocrites. Indeed, God is All-Knowing, All-Wise"
  33,2,Follow what is revealed to you from your Lord. Surely God is All-Aware of what you ňĻallňļ do
  33,3,"And put your trust in God, for God is sufficient as a Trustee of Affairs"
  33,4,"God does not place two hearts in any person‚Äôs chest. Nor does He regard your wives as ňĻunlawful for you likeňļ your real mothers, ňĻevenňļ if you say they are.¬†Nor does He regard your adopted children as your real children.¬†These are only your baseless assertions. But God declares the truth, and He ňĻaloneňļ guides to the ňĻRightňļ Way"
  33,5,"Let your adopted children keep their family names. That is more just in the sight of God. But if you do not know their fathers, then they are ňĻsimplyňļ your fellow believers and close associates. There is no blame on you for what you do by mistake, but ňĻonlyňļ for what you do intentionally. And God is All-Forgiving, Most Merciful"
  33,6,"The Prophet has a stronger affinity to the believers than they do themselves. And his wives are their mothers. As ordained by God, blood relatives are more entitled ňĻto inheritanceňļ than ňĻotherňļ believers and immigrants, unless you ňĻwant toňļ show kindness to your ňĻcloseňļ associates ňĻthrough bequestňļ.¬†This is decreed in the Record"
  33,7,"And ňĻrememberňļ when We took a covenant from the prophets, as well as from you ňĻO Prophetňļ, and from Noah, Abraham, Moses, and Jesus, son of Mary. We did take a solemn covenant from ňĻall ofňļ them"
  33,8,so that He may question these men of truth about their ňĻdelivery of theňļ truth. And He has prepared a painful punishment for the disbelievers
  33,9,"O believers! Remember God‚Äôs favour upon you when ňĻenemyňļ forces came to ňĻbesiegeňļ you ňĻin Medinaňļ,¬†so We sent against them a ňĻbitterňļ wind and forces you could not see.¬†And God is All-Seeing of what you do"
  33,10,"ňĻRememberňļ when they came at you from east and west,¬†when your eyes grew wild ňĻin horrorňļ and your hearts jumped into your throats, and you entertained ňĻconflictingňļ thoughts about God"
  33,11,"Then and there the believers were put to the test, and were violently shaken"
  33,12,"And ňĻrememberňļ when the hypocrites and those with sickness in their hearts said, ‚ÄúGod and His Messenger have promised us nothing but delusion!‚ÄĚ"
  33,13,"And ňĻrememberňļ when a group of them said, ‚ÄúO people of Yathrib!¬†There is no point in you staying ňĻhereňļ, so retreat!‚ÄĚ Another group of them asked the Prophet‚Äôs permission ňĻto leaveňļ, saying, ‚ÄúOur homes are vulnerable,‚ÄĚ while ňĻin factňļ they were not vulnerable. They only wished to flee"
  33,14,"Had their city been sacked from all sides and they had been asked to abandon faith, they would have done so with little hesitation"
  33,15,They had already pledged to God earlier never to turn their backs ňĻin retreatňļ. And a pledge to God must be answered for
  33,16,"Say, ňĻO Prophet,ňļ ‚ÄúFleeing will not benefit you if you ňĻtry toňļ escape a natural or violent death. ňĻIf it is not your time,ňļ you will only be allowed enjoyment for a little while.‚ÄĚ"
  33,17,"Ask ňĻthem, O Prophetňļ, ‚ÄúWho can put you out of God‚Äôs reach if He intends to harm you or show you mercy?‚ÄĚ They can never find any protector or helper besides God"